<!-- entry -->
	<h2 class="date-header">October 23, 2007</h2>


<div class="entry" id="entry-40612826">
			<h3 class="entry-header">Outlook 2007 search busted? Here's the fix</h3>
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<div class="entry-body">
			<p><a title="Halloween Porch" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/23649168@N00/1574792234/"><img alt="Halloween Porch" src="http://static.flickr.com/2347/1574792234_1d01aef9a7.jpg" border="0"></a></p> <p>Outlook without search is totally useless to me. I've run into a problem where Outlook reports "Search results may be incomplete because items are still being indexed". It then gives you some idea about how much work is left to do. The problem is that the work remaining never gets done; the indexer is wedged.</p> <p>Thanks to Serdar Yegulalp for <a href="http://searchexchange.techtarget.com/tip/0,289483,sid43_gci1256528,00.html">publishing this excellent set of instructions</a> for un-wedging Outlook 2007 search. Outlook is happily re-building its index as I type this.</p>

		</div>
		
					<script src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~s/LessIsBetter?i=http://www.iunknown.com/2007/10/outlook-2007-se.html" type="text/javascript"></script>
		
	</div>
	<div class="entry-footer">
					<p class="entry-footer-info">
				<span class="post-footers">Posted at 08:41 PM </span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://www.iunknown.com/2007/10/outlook-2007-se.html">Permalink</a>
			</p>
		
